"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-hodgkinson-storms-to-800m-gold-at-paris-2024-olympic-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Matt Hardy  Deputy Sports Editor - City AM  Keely Hodgkinsonstormed to track and field gold at the Paris 2024 Olympics on Monday to win Team GB their first solo athletics medal of the 33rd Olympiad.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Hardy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\"}, {\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999572537, \"rank\": 4.264062109358683e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old, who won a silver medal in Tokyo three years ago, held off her pre-race rival in the final - Mary Moraa of Kenya - to win her first Olympic gold in a time of 1:56.72.\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 387, \"end\": 392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.932872666969369, \"rank\": 0.07195765710043567, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 453, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_I_of_England\", \"score\": 0.6241688612637786, \"rank\": 0.5507832859439725, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_I_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_I_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 467, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9993416439995046, \"rank\": 0.0003306133068853308, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She became the first British 800m Olympic champion since Dame Kelly Holmes in 2004.\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.5472259255406158, \"rank\": 0.7884647473713903, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dame Kelly Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ethiopia's Tsige Duguma took home the silver, 0.5 seconds behind Brit Hodgkinson, with Moraa completing the podium.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.8705679063543275, \"rank\": 0.14867128643932254, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 683, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.9997305529349335, \"rank\": 0.0002695196862572764, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere it was first blood to Team GB in the velodrome after Katy Marchant, Sophie Capewell and Emma Finucane broke the world record to beat New Zealand and win gold in the women's team sprint.\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999572537, \"rank\": 4.264062109358683e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 793, \"end\": 806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}, {\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"score\": 0.999997246383526, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Capewell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\"}, {\"begin\": 828, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.6070881150116282, \"rank\": 0.6420264975281011, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}, {\"begin\": 873, \"end\": 884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\", \"score\": 0.40805292259028053, \"rank\": 0.7291653358012262, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City\\u202fAM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the third world record for the trio on Monday at a Velodrome which looks to be extremely quick.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But back on the track it was good news for Dina Asher-Smith, who recovered from a poor 100m showing to reach the finals of the 200m.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dina Asher-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She came second in her heat behind one of the event favourites Gabrielle Thomas.\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabrielle Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daryll Neita also reached the final with a solid performance in the third semi-final but Bianca Williams failed to progress.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1402, \"end\": 1414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daryll Neita\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\"}, {\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bianca_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bianca Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bianca_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bianca_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zharnel Hughes did not contest his 200m heat on Monday in the Stade de France after withdrawing with a tight hamstring.\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1536, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"score\": 0.5895021540821075, \"rank\": 0.6859730230311989, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He finished sixth in his 100m semi-final on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"No decision has been taken as yet in relation to his relay involvement,\\\" a British Athletics statement read.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.5472259255406158, \"rank\": 0.7884647473713903, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both of Team GB's female pole vaulters - Tokyo 2020 bronze medal winner Holly Bradshaw and world indoor champion Molly Caudery - failed to reach the final of their track and field event.\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1820, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999572537, \"rank\": 4.264062109358683e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1853, \"end\": 1858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.932872666969369, \"rank\": 0.07195765710043567, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1884, \"end\": 1889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holly_Flax\", \"score\": 0.7989309847998611, \"rank\": 0.24527055054490016, \"text\": \"Holly\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holly_Flax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holly_Flax\"}, {\"begin\": 1890, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terry_Bradshaw\", \"score\": 0.6479279325795023, \"rank\": 0.543381523884428, \"text\": \"Bradshaw\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terry_Bradshaw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terry_Bradshaw\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's honestly heartbreaking.\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not the experience I was hoping for and I am so sorry for everyone back home,\\\" said Caudery.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wish I could have done better, but I am going to try to learn from this and I will take everything I can from it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Tuesday at the Stade de France Josh Kerr goes for gold in the 1500m, aiming to beat his great rival Jakob Ingebrigtsen.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2261, \"end\": 2276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St